# Lab Architecture

Notes on how this lab is set up: hardware, VMs, and network layout.

## Host machine

Hostname: d01
User: lp01
OS: Ubuntu Server 24.04
Specs: 8 CPU cores, 6.9 GB RAM, 86 GB free disk
IP: 192.168.1.154 (local network)

## What's running

Wazuh SIEM (Manager, Indexer, Dashboard) installed directly on d01.

Wazuh is monitoring d01 itself right now through its own agent (agent.name: d01, 
agent.id: 000). Rootcheck, file integrity monitoring, and log analysis are all active 
as part of the default install.

## Planned additions

Kali Linux VM - will act as an attacker machine to generate real attack traffic for 
Wazuh to detect, instead of just watching d01 monitor itself. Once this is up, agent 
coverage will expand beyond just the SIEM host.

## Why this setup

The goal isn't a huge multi-VM enterprise simulation, it's to get real, hands-on 
experience running a SIEM: install it, tune it, watch real alerts come in, figure out 
which ones are noise and which ones matter, and document that process like an actual 
analyst would on the job.

## Network

Everything currently runs on the home local network (192.168.x.x range), no external 
exposure. Wazuh dashboard is accessed locally over HTTPS with a self-signed cert 
(browser will show "Not secure," which is expected for a lab environment without a 
trusted cert configured).
